<TITLE> Cabinet clears anti-terrorism law </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 19 (bdnews24.com)  The cabinet Thursday cleared the anti-terrorism and five other laws, enacted by the military-installed emergency government, for the parliament to ratify. The Anti-Terrorism Act, 2009 will allow the government to form a special tribunal to try terrorists and freeze the financial sources of the terrorists and terror organisations. The other ordinances approved are Finance Act, 2009 (for 2007-2008 budget); Finance Act, 2009 (for 2008-2009 budget); Padma Multi-purpose Bridge Project (land accusation) Act, 2009; Representation of the People Order (amendment) Act, 2009; and Finance Bill, 2009 (for Income Tax [amendment] Ordinance, 2007, Income Tax [second amendment] Ordinance, 2007, Income Tax [amendment] Ordinance, 2008 and Income Tax [second amendment] Ordinance, 2008). Prime minister Sheikh Hasina chaired the cabinet meeting. She directed authorities see to it that people who might have to incur losses due to the land acquisition for the bridge got fair price and faced no harassment, her press secretary Abul Kalam Azad told reporters after the meeting. About the RPO law, she said every detail of the provision of 'No Vote' would be scrutinised to decide whether it should remain. She said the provision of postal vote needed to be made effective. bdnews
